pageContext.claim: “But again, it looks like Florida is going to be in fantastic shape by comparison to what we thought. We thought it (Hurricane Dorian) was going to be a direct hit. We were thinking in terms of Andrew -- Hurricane Andrew -- from many years ago, where it went right through the middle of Miami, and that was a disaster.”
pageContext.analysis: Hurricane Andrew did hit Miami in 1992, but it did not go "right through the middle" of the city. Eugene Provenzo Jr., author of two books on Hurricane Andrew, told CNN, "The dense urban area of Miami was largely spared, as was Miami Beach."
